caption: An anthemic alternative rock track with jangly guitars, driving drums, and passionate male vocals. The production features layered guitar textures, dynamic shifts from quiet verses to explosive choruses, and emotionally charged lyrics about self-discovery.
lyrics:
[Intro]

[Verse 1]
Staring at the ceiling at 3 AM
Wondering how I got here again
All the paths I didn't take
All the choices I didn't make

[Verse 2]
Photographs of who I used to be
A stranger looking back at me
Somewhere along the way I lost my name
But I'm done playing their game

[Chorus]
I'm finding my way back to myself
Dusting off dreams from the shelf
No more hiding who I am
This is where my life began
Finding my way back

[Verse 3]
Burned the map they drew for me
Now I'm finally running free
Every scar tells a story
This is my territory

[Chorus]
I'm finding my way back to myself
Dusting off dreams from the shelf
No more hiding who I am
This is where my life began
Finding my way back

[Bridge]
It's never too late to start again
To rise up from where you've been

[Final Chorus]
I'm finding my way back to myself
This is where my life began
Finding my way back

[Outro]
